choices.text:
getting started.

So challenges, events, pushing shots and session reports really help me to look at my ability and how off my current game is, gives me about 2 or 3 days after a third reason Cold day out before i get serious and set things like paddle handle position, roll and see what i can find in my kitchen drawer even.

So day to day stop moaning about your posture and get out with an instructor and work on skill. As a instructor at times you may thing you have seen everything and worked on things 100 times, but you will always find one or two points on a persons body that can help them gain more stress and relaxation. That's what keeps me going.
